Greetings TESD Families,

We miss our students and staff tremendously and are anxiously awaiting returning to school for the 2020-2021 school year. We thank all families that filled out our end of the year survey and are now asking for additional input from you to better inform our decisions. Your feedback is important to us. Thank you for taking the time to complete this survey: https://bit.ly/ReturntoSchoolTESD

Saludos Familias TESD,

Extrañamos enormemente a nuestros estudiantes y al personal y estamos esperando ansiosamente regresar a la escuela para el año escolar 2020-2021. Agradecemos a todas las familias que llenaron nuestra encuesta de fin de año y ahora estamos solicitandole sus opinions adicionales para tomar mejores decisiones. Sus comentarios son importantes para nosotros. Gracias por tomarse el tiempo para completar esta encuesta: https://bit.ly/ReturntoSchoolTESD

post_text:
FREE WIFI from Cox Communications!!!

Cox Communications has an extensive network of wireless hotspots available at no charge.

To log onto a Cox hotspot:

•Open your device and power on.

• If not prompted with a WIFI selection, click on the time at the bottom right side of the screen..

•Click below the WIFI symbol where it says Not Connected

•Find the Cable WiFi or Cox WiFi wireless network from the list of available networks and connect to it.

• You will be taken to a screen in Chrome where you will need to accept the terms and conditions for services.. You will be prompted to enter your name, email address.
- check "I agree"

• You will not need to log in or register

• Note that this is NOT a secured network.

• For a map of available hotspots, go to: https://www.cox.com/residential/internet/learn/cox-hotspots.html?fbclid=IwAR2UpNPnpp1HRkQ-T0ltzxUEnbOKy6xQ33a8secv1JjWnxxsDYrWv34h4Uw

post_text: Dear Tolleson Elementary School District Community, this is a reminder that to ensure the health and safety of our students, families and staff to the best of our ability, our schools will be closed beginning March 16th for two weeks. We will continue to evaluate the situation carefully and inform you if further closure is necessary.
text: Dear Tolleson Elementary School District Community, this is a reminder that to ensure the health and safety of our students, families and staff to the best of our ability, our schools will be closed beginning March 16th for two weeks. We will continue to evaluate the situation carefully and inform you if further closure is necessary.

post_text:
This is an update from the School Board Meeting held on March 14, 2020 at 5:00 pm. The Tolleson Elementary School District School Board and Leadership Team ensures the health and safety of our students and staff remain at the forefront of all decisions.
At this time, all Tolleson Elementary Schools (including preschool, childcare, and all before and after school activities) will be CLOSED for at least two weeks to support all efforts to minimize the spread of COVID-19 (Coronavirus).
We will continue to communicate with families via our website (www.tollesonschools.com) and social media accounts.
Information on food services and instruction will be posted on the website by 8:00 am on Monday, March 16, 2020.
